org.hkijena.jipipe.api.registries

Class JIPipeDatatypeRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.registries.JIPipeDatatypeRegistry

  • public class JIPipeDatatypeRegistry
extends Object
    Contains known JIPipeData types, and associates them to their respective JIPipeDataSlot.

        public static boolean isTriviallyConvertible(Class<? extends JIPipeData> inputDataType,
                                             Class<? extends JIPipeData> outputDataType)
        Returns true if the input data type can be trivially converted into the output data type. A trivial conversion is applied when the input data is the same as the output data type or inherits from it.
        Parameters:
        inputDataType - the input data type
        outputDataType - the output data type
        Returns:
        if the output data type can be assigned from the input data type without any explicit conversion rules
